          <h2 style="font-size:24px;line-height:1.2;font-weight:500; margin-top:2px !important">North Korea-South Korean standoff</h2>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-image border-radius="10px" padding="10px 12px" width="600px" src="https://www.geopoliticalsummary.com/email/images/us-army-soldiers-cross-hantan-river-training-yeoncheon-south-korea-north-korea-border.png" alt="US Army soldiers prepare to cross the Hantan River at a training field in Yeoncheon, South Korea, near the border with North Korea" href="https://www.geopoliticalsummary.com" />
        <mj-text padding="0px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#A9A7AF">
          <p style="font-size: 12px; line-height: 1.2; color: #A9A7AF;"><i>US Army soldiers prepare to cross the Hantan River at a training field in Yeoncheon, South Korea, near the border with North Korea. Credits: Ahn Young-joon/AP</i></p>
        </mj-text> 

        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
         
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">South Korea’s military reported on Monday that <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-11-03-2025-h1-1-north-korea-fired-multiple-unidentified-ballistic-missiles" target="_blank">North Korea fired multiple unidentified ballistic missiles</a>. They fired them from Hwanghae province into the West Sea. This missile launch occurred concurrently with South Korea and the US beginning their annual joint military drill. Pyongyang has consistently opposed these drills, calling them rehearsals for invasion, and routinely responds with weapons tests of its own.</p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">The drill, which the two countries describe as defensive, involves live, virtual, and field-based training and will run until March 20. Pyongyang warned that such activities could escalate tensions and lead to accidental conflict. The incident comes after a recent accident in which two South Korean Air Force fighter jets dropped bombs on a village during joint training with the US. 
       </p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">The incident injured 31 people. The relationship between North and South Korea continues to deteriorate. North Korea continues its missile tests and violation of UN sanctions. The two countries have technically been at war since their conflict ended. However, an armistice ended the conflict, not an actual peace treaty.
</p>
        </mj-text>
