        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="TNYAdobeCaslonPro, 'Times New Roman', serif;" color="#000000">
          <h2 style="font-size:24px;line-height:1.2;font-weight:500;">Romanian candidate banned</h2>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-image border-radius="10px" padding="10px 12px" width="600px" src="https://www.geopoliticalsummary.com/email/images/calin-georgescu-independent-presidential-candidate-bucharest-romania.png" alt="Calin Georgescu, who ran as an independent presidential candidate, is pictured in Bucharest, Romania" href="https://www.geopoliticalsummary.com" />
        <mj-text padding="0px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#A9A7AF">
          <p style="font-size: 12px; line-height: 1.2; color: #A9A7AF;"><i>Calin Georgescu, who ran as an independent presidential candidate, is pictured in Bucharest, Romania. Credits: Alexandru Dobre/AP</i></p>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000"> 
         
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">Romania's electoral commission has <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-11-03-2025-h2-2-banned-far-right-politician-calin-georgescu" target="_blank">banned far-right politician Calin Georgescu</a> from running in the upcoming presidential elections. A specific reason wasn't given, but his independent candidacy was rejected. Georgescu called the decision a blow to democracy and claimed that Romania was under tyranny. He vowed to appeal the decision. "Europe is now a dictatorship, Romania is under tyranny!" he added. 
</p>

          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">Hundreds of his supporters clashed with police in Bucharest, attempting to breach the electoral commission's building. The protests turned violent, with protesters throwing stones and setting fire to furniture in nearby cafes. Seven arrests had been made, and 13 police officers were injured in the violence. While leading in opinion polls, Georgescu faced legal challenges.</p>

          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">Some challenges include accusations of ties to Russia and various charges such as campaign financing violations. He is also accused of promoting fascist ideologies. Despite the controversies, Georgescu's supporters are furious with the decision. US figures like Elon Musk and Vice President JD Vance have criticized the decision. They called it an attack on democratic principles and an effort to suppress the popular will.</p>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-divider border-width="1px" border-style="solid" border-color="lightgrey" padding="0px 12px" />
      </mj-column>
    </mj-section>
