        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="TNYAdobeCaslonPro, 'Times New Roman', serif;" color="#000000">
          <h2 style="font-size:24px;line-height:1.2;font-weight:500;">Musk takes on Poland</h2>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size:18px;line-height:1.5;"><strong>Summary: Poland's Donald Tusk defends Foreign Minister Radosław Sikorski after Musk calls him a 'small man' over the issue of using the Starlink Satellite system in Ukraine.</strong></p>

          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">US Secretary of State Marco Rubio and tech billionaire Elon Musk feuded with Polish FM Radosław Sikorski over using Musk's Starlink satellite system in Ukraine. The debate started when Sikorski commented on Musk's post <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/ps-11-03-2025-h3-3-about-potentially-turning-off-the-system" target="_blank">about potentially turning off the system</a>, which provides vital internet to Ukraine, especially in war zones. Sikorski warned that if SpaceX became unreliable, Poland would seek other suppliers.</p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">The Polish government funds part of the country's 42,000 Starlink terminals. Musk angrily called Sikorski a "small man" in response. Rubio rejected Sikorski’s claims and told him to be grateful for Starlink. Polish PM Donald Tusk defended Sikorski, emphasizing respect for international partners, saying, "True leadership means respect for partners and allies. Even for the smaller and weaker ones. Never arrogance. Dear friends, think about it."</p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">Meanwhile, the ruling conservative Law and Justice party criticized Sikorski's comments. Some even suggested his Twitter presence should be reconsidered. Starlink terminals are crucial to Ukraine’s military operations. The European Commission is exploring alternatives to prevent Musk from using the service as leverage in peace talks in the future.</p>
        </mj-text>
    </mj-section>
