          <p style="font-size:18px;line-height:1.5;">
            <strong>🇷🇺 Russia expels two British diplomats for alleged spying</strong>
          </p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">Russia has expelled a British diplomat and the spouse of another diplomat. Russia is accusing them of "<a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-11-03-2025-br2-5-intelligence-and-subversive-work" target="_blank">intelligence and subversive work.</a>" The Federal Security Service (FSB) stripped them of their accreditation and gave them two weeks to leave the country. The UK Foreign Office dismissed the accusations as baseless.</p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">This move followed a series of diplomatic expulsions between the two countries. The UK expelled a Russian diplomat last month in response to Moscow’s actions in 2024. Diplomatic ties between the UK and Russia have soured since Russia invaded Ukraine. Prime Minister Sir Keir Starmer is leading efforts to support Ukraine and pledging to increase defense spending.</p>
        </mj-text>
