          <h2 style="font-size:24px;line-height:1.2;font-weight:500; margin-top:2px !important">Why does Poland contribute so much to NATO?</h2>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-image border-radius="10px" padding="10px 12px" width="600px" src="https://www.geopoliticalsummary.com/email/images/poland-nato-member-nations-view.png" alt="A view of Poland as a part of the nations that together form NATO" href="https://www.geopoliticalsummary.com" />
        <mj-text padding="0px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#A9A7AF">
          <p style="font-size: 12px; line-height: 1.2; color: #A9A7AF;"><i>A view of Poland as a part of the nations that together form NATO. </i></p>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">Poland contributes the most to <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-11-03-2025-f1-6-natos-military-budget" target="_blank">NATO’s military budget</a>, percentage-wise than all the members of the NATO BLOC. In 2024, it contributed over 4%, has vowed to commit to over 5%, and has urged other Europeans to do the same. Poland has been a strong contributor to NATO’s operations in regions such as Afghanistan, Iraq, and Kosovo.
</p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">
          While it has been critical of Donald Trump’s policies toward Ukraine, it still has tried to stay in the US’s good graces compared to other European countries. Poland has an extensive history of invasions and occupations, especially during and after World War II. These invasions have made Poland protective of its sovereignty and security. Poland was under Soviet influence for much of the Cold War and suffered during the period when it was part of the Warsaw Pact. </p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">The end of the Cold War and the fall of the Soviet Union left Poland eager to avoid repeating history. Poland also has strong ties to the Polish-American community, so the transatlantic connection is also instilled. This community is one of the largest and most influential immigrant groups in the United States, and their ties to Poland remain strong in various aspects.</p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">Polish Americans advocated for Polish causes during the Cold War. Poland's location in the heart of Central Europe, bordering Germany to the west and Russia (via Kaliningrad) to the east, is strategically crucial for NATO’s defense strategy. It sees itself as one of the frontlines of defense if Russia attacks the European Union.</p>
          
        </mj-text>
